'''SolTrans''', officially '''Solano County Transit''', is  a [[Joint Powers Authority]] that provides [[public transportation]] service to the southern [[Solano County]] cities of [[Vallejo, California|Vallejo]] and [[Benicia, California|Benicia]]. SolTrans was established in 2011 and is the result of a [[merger]] between '''Vallejo Transit''' and '''Benicia Breeze'''.<ref name=Rohrs0726>{{cite news|last=Rohrs|first=Sarah|title=Huge deficit already saddles merged SolTrans bus system serving Benicia and Vallejo|url=http://www.timesheraldonline.com/ci_18550242|accessdate=3 August 2011|newspaper=Vallejo Times Herald|date=26 July 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/60fajLQPG|archivedate=26 July 2011}}</ref>

==Services==
SolTrans provides local and express bus service to the Solano County cities of [[Vallejo, California|Vallejo]], [[Benicia, California|Benicia]], and [[Fairfield, California]]. It also provides express bus service to the [[Contra Costa County, California|Contra Costa County]] communities of [[El Cerrito, California|El Cerrito]] and [[Walnut Creek, California|Walnut Creek]], providing regional connections to [[Bay Area Rapid Transit|BART]]. SolTrans also provides complementary ADA paratransit.

Ferry service from Vallejo to [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco]], which was operated by Vallejo Transit, is now provided by [[San Francisco Bay Ferry]], the public operating arm of the San Francisco Bay Area Water Emergency Transportation Authority [WETA].<ref>[http://leginfo.ca.gov/cgi-bin/postquery?bill_number=sb_976&sess=CUR&house=B&author=torlakson SB 976: San Francisco Bay Area Water Emergency Transportation Authority]</ref>

==Connections==
SolTrans connects with the following public transit services:

* [[AC Transit]]
* [[Bay Area Rapid Transit|BART]]
* [[County Connection]] (Contra Costa)
* [[Fairfield and Suisun Transit]]
* [[Golden Gate Transit]]
* [[San Francisco Bay Ferry]]
* [[Vine Transit]] (Napa)
* [[WestCAT]] (Contra Costa)

==Vehicles and routes==
SolTrans operates a mixed fleet of buses. The full service local routes feature [[Gillig]] low-floor hybrid buses, <ref>http://www.mtc.ca.gov/news/current_topics/8-11/soltrans.htm</ref> while the intercity routes use [[Motor Coach Industries|MCI]] D-4500 buses. SolTrans also makes use of [[Starcraft Bus]] Starlite shuttles for Paratransit and Dial-a-ride services. All buses are bicycle and wheelchair accessible.<ref>[[Motor Bus Society]], [http://www.motorbussociety.org/conventn/05spr/index.html Convention Report, Spring 2005]. April 18, 2005</ref> As of 18 August 2012, SolTrans operates seventeen bus routes. Seven routes operate within Vallejo, four serve as supplemental routes for local school students in Vallejo and Benicia, and five are intercity routes with one being a supplemental shuttle bus for [[Baylink Ferry]] service.<ref>http://baylinkferry.com/schedule/baylink-bus.php</ref> General transit within Benicia is provided through a SolTrans-branded [[dial-a-ride]] service. Unless otherwise noted, routes operate weekdays and Saturday.

